          "questionText": "Gold and silver are mixed in the ratio $3 : 7$ by mass to make an alloy.\nA bar of alloy has mass $450$ g.\nWork out the mass of gold in the bar.",
          "marks": 3,
          "commandWord": "find",
          "answerType": "integer",
          "correctAnswer": "135",
          "tolerance": null,
          "unit": "g",
          "markScheme": [
            { "mark": "M1", "desc": "Total parts: $3 + 7 = 10$" },
            { "mark": "M1", "desc": "One part: $450 \\div 10 = 45$ g" },
            { "mark": "A1", "desc": "Gold: $3 \\times 45 = 135$ g cao" }
          ],
          "workingSteps": [
            "Total parts: $3 + 7 = 10$",
            "One part: $450 \\div 10 = 45$ g",
            "Gold: $3 \\times 45 = 135$ g"
          ]
        },
        {
          "label": "b",
          "questionText": "Gold costs $\\$55$ per gram and silver costs $\\$0.80$ per gram.\nWork out the cost of making the $450$ g bar.",
